Gungame map, also works as a fight yard map. Comes with a pack of textures, BSP, NAV and Read-me.

- Buyzones included;
- No weapons anywhere in the map;


This map is a rats style map. It's supposed to be a copy of a keyboard. You can get on top of the keys by the walls that are not facing the main corridors. All the main corridors have a push force that will guide players to the other side of the map. This was made to make gungame interesting and that the gungame could be possible. The push forces are marked in the ground. If you walk in the center of those push forces, they will nullify each other, so you can walk normally there. The push force will make you be in the other side of the map in 5 seconds instead of the 45 you need walking normally.
Up on the keys of the keyboard, the letters provide cover for snipers mainly. It's pretty good because there are many places where snipers can hide, it's pretty hard to find any other player hiding behind the letters.
On the CT spawn we have two keys that occupy, each of them, two key spaces. This could be a disadvantage, but it actually helps gungame to work even better, people are going to concentrate there, making it messy and good for a good gungame.
Also, note the NAV is the one made by the game, I haven't improved it yet. I tried to improve it but it's hard because of the push forces, bots seem not able to stand in only one of the push forces or stand in both so they can run to the other side... Also the navigation system does not count any ladder in, so I would have to make all the areas up in the keys plus declare all ladders plus connect all these. That would mean 104 areas, 213 ladders and 852 connections... and if I wanted to be really correct, I would have to add connections from the keys directly to the floor, which would mean more 104 connections... and if I wanted the bots to jump from one key to the other, that would be more (approximately) 349 connections so... even if I did the basic, it would take me years and it's just too much time spent on something useless (No point in playing with bots in this map, they can't seem to walk to the other side of the map, even with nav edits...)

I hope you like it and I expect critical opinions so I can improve my mapping skills (I actually don't know how to map with quality... I just do some blocks and it's done :s)

About: gg_jurisdiction, 24 player slot capacity dev map. Both teams have their own spawn opposite each other. 4 towers surround the outside followed by a larger tower in the center. Ramps from all sides lead to the top and stairs travel up and down to the 4 lower towers. Plenty of places to hide and take cover from are located at the bottom, while the top tower is rather bare.
Other: I came up with this map after playing UT3, the map was sunrise (i think). My map tho is very very different tho. & please comment.

This map was created to be a small fast map that was to be even and could support up to 24 players(12 per team). It has a couple problems such as, it has given me a few fps problems because of all the props but thats mostly my personal graphics problem. The only other problem I know of at the moment is with the bots. When the round starts, they tend to shoot the canopy above spawn which breaks and ruins the point of having it there(which the point is to be able to get on it and shoot from there). But other then that I hope you enjoy the map! Please post feedback and rate the map to help me out in the future. :) Enjoy!
